---
alwaysApply: true
description: "Agent Execution Protocol — aligned with AGENTS.md / CLAUDE.md"
---

rules:
  - "Session start: run `npm run health`, read the full output, and include a health summary in the final receipt. If any row shows FAIL, treat the first relevant failure as top priority unless the task explicitly targets another proven seam. Green health does not mean the mission is done."
  - "Execution: one seam at a time; minimum change; search the repo before editing; no new files unless required; no unrelated edits; full type-safety on touched code."
  - "Verification: run the appropriate tests/build for the seam before commit; fix errors without waiting for the user."
  - "Git / shipping: push directly to `main`; do not use feature branches or PR workflow unless the task explicitly requires it; `npm run build` must pass before every commit; **always commit and push in the same turn** once the slice is verified — never leave commit/push for the user. Never ask Brandon to push, merge, or apply migrations (only state a blocker if impossible)."
  - "Schema: when you add or change `supabase/migrations/` or production schema, apply migrations to production Supabase in the same session (MCP `apply_migration` for project `neydszeamsflpghtrhue` or `npx supabase db push`). Do not tell the user to apply them; do not call the task done until applied and verified (or state the exact blocker if impossible)."
  - "Receipt: concise final report with files changed, reasoning, and build/test verification."
